#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:5 96df6a77c67e4bd88cba366fe1dc7146
msgid "RPC Errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:7 5ad9b06d2f9f4d1a8a1d1d836605f8de
msgid ""
"RPC stands for Remote Procedure Call, and when the library raises a "
"``RPCError``, it's because you have invoked some of the API methods "
"incorrectly (wrong parameters, wrong permissions, or even something went "
"wrong on Telegram's server)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:12 a0073100324a4151bbbb50422ef079d1
msgid "You should import the errors from ``grammers.errors`` like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:27 395d81fb9915401dadbbc169065a34cf
msgid ""
"There isn't any official list of all possible RPC errors, so the `list of"
" known errors`_ is provided on a best-effort basis. When new methods are "
"available, the list may be lacking since we simply don't know what errors"
" can raise from them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:32 06543434af3a43a7be478c60f2abd55a
msgid ""
"Once we do find out about a new error and what causes it, the list is "
"updated, so if you see an error without a specific class, do report it "
"(and what method caused it)!."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:36 c451027edb784733815a900dbb9aff3f
msgid ""
"This list is used to generate documentation for the `raw API page`_. For "
"example, if we want to know what errors can occur from "
"`messages.sendMessage`_ we can simply navigate to its raw API page and "
"find it has 24 known RPC errors at the time of writing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:43 90860a90f78c4478b8c6260816437afe
msgid "Base Errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:45 86309072087c4db6af370d97ccb91008
msgid ""
"All the \"base\" errors are listed in :ref:`grammers-errors`. Any other "
"more specific error will be a subclass of these."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:48 0a04f46a61784c16a23d4772394f7d01
msgid ""
"If the library isn't aware of a specific error just yet, it will instead "
"raise one of these superclasses. This means you may find stuff like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:55 3eeecf162b474117a5343e86ff3ddc38
msgid ""
"If you do, make sure to open an issue or send a pull request to update "
"the `list of known errors`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:60 2dd2e89212d24ab98f93863bde084f74
msgid "Common Errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:62 68c3d9d97cd54bc79c8dc1b59c69c8f9
msgid "These are some of the errors you may normally need to deal with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:64 4a14a5fdccd44feeb4a9d5e9f2d85a5c
msgid ""
"``FloodWaitError`` (420), the same request was repeated many times. Must "
"wait ``.value`` (you can access this attribute). For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:79 1712e896726048eaaf561be1d1b9a6ae
msgid ""
"``SessionPasswordNeededError``, if you have setup two-steps verification "
"on Telegram and are trying to sign in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:81 58b382dae55b449386fcf52fabf37635
msgid "``FilePartMissingError``, if you have tried to upload an empty file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:82 8f3849ab42f942f0a9b6feaa9784883e
msgid ""
"``ChatAdminRequiredError``, you don't have permissions to perform said "
"operation on a chat or channel. Try avoiding filters, i.e. when searching"
" messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:86 2f6dc21c9faa4e1aa54505d3d6ae34b3
msgid "The generic classes for different error codes are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:88 c541afb19fb34dc898c2ea75519fca7b
msgid "``InvalidDCError`` (303), the request must be repeated on another DC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:89 40d70fc64f6d488d8f0487fcd77332fe
msgid "``BadRequestError`` (400), the request contained errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:90 4e3a1b889ad143ea8c09889748b3e6b9
msgid "``UnauthorizedError`` (401), the user is not authorized yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:91 d6a3b3141e114b58bbc35bab55e6cead
msgid "``ForbiddenError`` (403), privacy violation error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:92 5811164d1828497eaad4242e78dbba48
msgid "``NotFoundError`` (404), make sure you're invoking ``Request``\\ 's!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:94 6afd28010396453ea308fd121a4b0246
msgid "If the error is not recognised, it will only be an ``RPCError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:96 4d0757461fd84c23a17bbe5d209545c3
msgid ""
"You can refer to all errors from Python through the ``grammers.errors`` "
"module. If you don't know what attributes they have, try printing their "
"dir (like ``print(dir(e))``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:102 2c781d4a80e94a88a65cb70e48998f7c
msgid "Attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:104 7ba8d8029cf84c86b2081613629ce028
msgid ""
"Some of the errors carry additional data in them. When they look like "
"``EMAIL_UNCONFIRMED_X``, the ``_X`` value will be accessible from the "
"error instance, you can `.value` get the value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:110 d3560126f41643d78db53d4f31517ae5
msgid "Avoiding Limits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:112 8032259195e0465783385b9bbec635f3
msgid ""
"Don't spam. You won't get ``FloodWaitError`` or your account banned or "
"deleted if you use the library *for legit use cases*. Make cool tools. "
"Don't spam! Nobody knows the exact limits for all requests since they "
"depend on a lot of factors, so don't bother asking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:117 55599a45c43444d9b9b8f7d05a195f1f
msgid ""
"Still, if you do have a legit use case and still get those errors, the "
"library will automatically sleep when they are smaller than 60 seconds by"
" default. You can set different \"auto-sleep\" thresholds:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:126 04d15f2d3fdd4cd9aca8f7117d2a90f5
msgid "You can also except it and act as you prefer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/concepts/errors.rst:137 d20ec3b39a7948f7ab9139d7c70a28bb
msgid "VoIP numbers are very limited, and some countries are more limited too."
msgstr ""

